{
  "text": "In Fe-rich enriched cores it appeared that infauna stimulated transport of iron from the deeper sediment towards the sediment surface. TRFe increased by 48% in the upper 4 cm, corresponding to an upward Fe flux > 30 times higher than previously estimated for diffusion-controlled Fe-rich sediments ). Thus, [CITATION_1] found that Fe 2+ for TRIS formation was primarily mobilized within the zone of SR. Our results suggest that Fe is transported in bioturbated sediment, presumably as Fe",
